Since my image was published and [the] public was incited against me [] many people have attempted [to attack me].
These criminals after us are people who are [] associated with powers that be in Ghana and can do anything and get away with it.
Indeed, it [has] been hinted in some quarters that the very man who published [my image] said he was doing everything possible to quell [my] existence.
MPs words have power
Agyapong, a member of the ruling New Patriotic Party, has served as an MP for 19 years.
