Agyapong justified his actions and said his comments were not meant to provoke harm and referred to a skirmish. Divela allegedly once had with one of Agypongs staff members.
In another video, Agyapong suggests that Anas is actually a prime suspect in Divelas death.
He offered to pay a 100,000 Ghanaian Cedi reward (about 19,000 US dollars) for anyone who finds Divelas killers as proof that he did not call for his murder.
